    "summary": "In everything I do, I want to have genuine impact. If it\u2019s not future proof, I will not choose it. If it doesn\u2019t add value, I\u2019ll keep looking for something better. The road of quality and reliability is hard to travel, but it\u2019s the route of my values.\nWith 25 years of experience, I have become quite allround. From branding to management and from lobbying to hrm; I plunged in. My work took me to all possible levels: local - national - international.\nAs director of the Dutch National Youth Council, I gathered unique insights into the motivations and aspirations of youth. I learned how to develop their talents, and how to involve them in activities and organizations. That, and a firm belief in the future, is what I carry away, to new ventures.\nWhat gives me energy, is using my sharp mind and stirring up my visionary and creative powers. Catch the essence and uncover mechanisms, that\u2019s the start. From there, you can design your way to success, avoiding confusion about ends or means, adding value or hitting targets, going for a win or avoiding a loss.\nAs entrepreneur and investor, I support a young designer in the launch of the new brand Merus Fashion. Sustainable, fair and handcrafted. Elegant minimalism, about to conquer the world, from Canggu, Bali.\nIn addition, I\u2019m open to work at companies with the same objective: to bring great things into the world.",
